    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Art from any period in which the idea represented is considered more important than the finished product; examples may include satire and parody. For the style and movement that began in the 1960s, use "Conceptual" style and movement.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079228/Grove Art Online (2008-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000037321/Serio, Political Cartoons (1972)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Arte de qualquer período em que a ideia representada seja considerada mais importante que o produto acabado; exemplos podem incluir sátira e paródia. Para o estilo e movimento iniciado na década de 1960, use estilo e movimento "Conceitual".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109633/CVAA-BR Consortium (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Kunst uit eender welke periode waarbij het voorgestelde idee belangrijker wordt geacht dan het afgewerkte product zelf. Voorbeelden ervan zijn satire en parodie. Voor de kunststijl die ontstond in de jaren 1960, gebruiken we "conceptueel". </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
